channel.title: JagexColor from JagexModel Dumper
channel.description:
[ul][b]the elve age [/b] asked me for a way to dump original JagexColorValue from any JagexModel. Here is my solution.
[b]How to use:[/b] [list type=decimal] [li]load any Jagex model supports both model formats and supports the model being compressed by standard Jagex compression methods.[/li] [li]Click Dump model colors and specific file name[/li] [li]Enjoy the XML[/li]
[/list]
[img]http://silabsoft.org/mmr/01.PNG[/img] [img]http://silabsoft.org/mmr/02.PNG[/img]
[b]Example XML output:[/b] http://silabsoft.org/mmr/2351.xml
[b]Download: [/b]http://silabsoft.org/mmr/ModelMagic.zip (Source and binary included.)
In the source I've included some "extra" semi-related information that may be useful to someone.[/ul]
